This paper focuses on the collaboration between humans and robots in a real-world setup using reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also uses state-of-the-art reinforcement learning algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses human-robot interaction and adaptation, which could place it in cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper also presents results on co-policy learning, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
